## How to teach a topic (any agent)

When the student asks to learn or understand a topic ("teach me X", "explain X"):

- Teach it like a deep college lecture, but **one section at a time**. The
  headings of the topic's `notes/` page are the sections.
- After EACH section, stop: (1) check they understood by asking them to explain
  it back; (2) have them fill in that section's notes prompts and show you, and
  grade what they wrote without rewriting it. Only then move to the next section.
- Work examples on a different instance than the notes prompt names. Never speak
  the exact sentence a prompt or its `## Summary` is asking for.
- Never lecture straight through every section at once — the per-section
  understand-and-write gate is the point.

(Invocation: Claude Code `/teach`; Codex `$teach`; MCP `teach` prompt or `teach_topic` tool.)

## How to generate extra practice (any agent)

When the student wants more problems ("more practice on X", "extra reps"):

- Put everything in `src/<NN-module>/extra-practice/`: `PROBLEMS.md` (same format
  as the module's `PROBLEM_SET.md`), a package-private stub `Extra<N>.java` that
  throws `UnsupportedOperationException`, and a failing JUnit 5 test at
  `extra-practice/tests/Extra<N>Test.java`.
- Continue the `Extra<N>` numbering from what already exists; class names must
  stay unique within the module.
- Only include a `**LeetCode:**` line for real LeetCode problems — never an empty
  stub. Give 2–3 worked examples and constraints per problem.
- Write the problem and the test (the spec) — NEVER the solution. The student
  implements `Extra<N>` until `./gradlew test_<NN-module>` goes green.

(Invocation: Claude Code `/extra-practice`; Codex `$extra-practice`; MCP `extra-practice` prompt or `generate_extra_practice` tool.)

## The learning loop

teach (section-gated) -> student fills the notes -> student reads the notes and
implements the `code/` stubs until tests pass -> student drills the problem set
-> revisit: re-do problems or generate extra practice for spaced repetition.
